.TH "NAVIGATION.CURRENTENTRYCHANGE_EVENT" "3JS" "January 7, 2026" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
Navigation.currententrychange_event \- Navigation: currententrychange
event
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]currententrychange\f[B]\f[R] event of the
\f[CR]Navigation\f[R] interface is fired when the
\f[CR]Navigation.currentEntry\f[R] has changed.
.PP
This event will fire for:
.IP \(bu 2
Same\-document navigations (e.g., \f[CR]back()\f[R] or
\f[CR]traverseTo()\f[R]).
.IP \(bu 2
Replacements (i.e., a \f[CR]navigate()\f[R] call with \f[CR]history\f[R]
set to \f[CR]replace\f[R]).
.IP \(bu 2
Other calls that change the entry\(cqs state (e.g.,
\f[CR]updateCurrentEntry()\f[R], or the History API\(cqs
\f[CR]History.replaceState()\f[R]).
.PP
This event fires after the navigation is committed, meaning that the
visible URL has changed and the \f[CR]NavigationHistoryEntry\f[R] update
has occurred.
It is useful for migrating from usage of older API features like the
\f[CR]hashchange\f[R] or \f[CR]popstate\f[R] events.
.SH SYNTAX
Use the event name in methods like \f[CR]addEventListener()\f[R], or set
an event handler property.
.IP
.EX
addEventListener(\(dqcurrententrychange\(dq, (event) => { })

oncurrententrychange = (event) => { }
.EE
.SH EVENT TYPE
A \f[CR]NavigationCurrentEntryChangeEvent\f[R].
Inherits from \f[CR]Event\f[R].
.SH EXAMPLES
Navigation data reporting:
.IP
.EX
navigation.addEventListener(\(dqcurrententrychange\(dq, () \f[B]=>\f[R] {
  \f[B]const\f[R] data = navigation.currentEntry.getState();
  submitAnalyticsData(data.analytics);
});
.EE
.PP
Setting up a per\-entry event:
.IP
.EX
navigation.addEventListener(\(dqcurrententrychange\(dq, () \f[B]=>\f[R] {
  navigation.currentEntry.addEventListener(\(dqdispose\(dq, genericDisposeHandler);
});
.EE
